HEADWORD: Overflourish
<hw>O`ver*flour"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make excessive display or flourish of.</def>
<rj><au>Collier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To embellish with outward ornaments or flourishes;
to varnish over.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overflow</ent>⟦br⟧
